Pine trees are called evergreens because their needles stay for around 2 years.
Pine tree needle's length varies from 1 inch to 11 inches long. 
Male and female pine trees both produce needle covered cones.

Willow trees can grow up to a whole 70 feet tall. 
Their crown(or width) can also be 70 feet because of the broad branches that stretch out.

Oak trees can lives 100s of years, even 1000s. They also produce up to 10 million acorns in their life time.
They are one of the tallest trees reaching heights to about 148 feet.

Maple trees are the trees that produce the maple syrup we use on our pancakes. 
Their leaves change many colors throughout the year as well.